power was restored to downtown and residential 
areas early sunday after a blackout caused by an explosion in a 
transformer vault that also knocked out telephone operator service 
to parts of three states 
three utility workers were critically burned 
about 13000 volts of electricity were running through the 
underground equipment when a flash fire sparked the explosion 
forcing the evacuation of neighboring us west communications and 
atampt buildings officials said 
you can imagine thats pretty powerful assistant fire chief 
bill mcdonnell said of the voltage 
two of the victims who were in the vault at the time of the 
blast a man and a woman breathed in fire and were in very 
critical condition sunday at st joseph hospital in omaha nursing 
supervisor becke majors said the third worker a man was at 
another hospital in serious condition 
