<TEXT>
two of television comedys most familiar 
fathers robert young of father knows best and fred macmurray of 
my three sons spent a lowkey fathers day 
young who as the venerable jim anderson regularly solved family 
crises within a halfhour from 1954 to 1963 spent the day at home 
