should have notified security personnel and airport police about 
burkes dismissal three weeks before distributed a photo of him and 
change locks to which he had keys 
defendants say nothing came to their attention to warrant such 
action 
defense attorneys also have tried to point out that burkes 
considerable temper was largely limited to arguments with his 
girlfriend away from the job 
bottom said he has concluded that burke managed to sneak the gun 
past the security checkpoint by concealing it under clothing and 
using his identification badge to avoid metal detectors 
defense attorneys have alluded to an fbi report not yet admitted 
into evidence that suggests burke used the airports back stairways 
and halls to reach the public storage lockers in the secure area of 
the terminal 
the fbi report said the use of employeeonly hallways and stairs 
combined with wearing a usair employee badge to avoid suspicion 
would have been the least obtrusive way to bypass security 
