five islands and made the area unfit for habitation for 33 years 
residents living on other islands downwind from the blasts moved out 
as recently as 1985 for fear of continued radiation 
a federal appeals court here ruled that the 1983 agreement 
supported by legislation that took effect in 1986 bars island 
inhabitants from suing the united states for additional compensation 
we are unpersuaded that judicial intervention is appropriate at 
this time on the mere speculation that the alternative remedy may 
prove to be inadequate the appeals court said 
the case is people of enewetak vs us 881466 
