be a considerable degree of continuity in the us position while 
not ruling out some adjustments 
one new element is a us proposal for onsite trial inspections 
to monitor some cuts of longrange ballistic missiles already 
written into a draft treaty washington officials said a pentagon 
official said bush wants to take advantage of the new soviet 
openness 
it would be the first time in superpower arms control that 
verification begins during talks rather than once a treaty is 
completed 
but neither side has hinted at movement on disputes over the 
pentagons spacebased star wars missile defense sealaunched 
cruise missiles and mobile landbased missiles 
the soviets say the us missile shield or strategic defense 
initiative violates the 1972 superpower antiballistic missile 
treaty 
