staff has predicted protracted and agonizing negotiations 
much of a draft treaty to cut each sides longrange or 
strategic nuclear forces by 30 to 50 percent has been agreed in 
previous rounds 
start is intended to cover nuclear weapons with which the 
superpowers can strike each other including those considered most 
dangerous sea and landbased ballistic missiles and heavy bombers 
delegates are to begin the new session by reviewing agreements 
already contained in the 400page draft text 
among the agreements in earlier rounds are lowered ceilings of 
6000 nuclear warheads and 1600 delivery vehicles missiles and 
bombers for each side outlines of a system for monitoring 
compliance were also set 
