face challenges from radical rivals such as interior minister ali 
akbar mohtashemi and possibly khomeinis son ahmad 43 who has 
shown increased political ambitions in recent months 
the pragmatists are said to favor ending irans isolation and 
opening up the economy to wider free enterprise mainly to secure 
foreign aid for irans reconstruction program following a ceasefire 
in the 8year war with iraq 
the antiwestern radicals seek to tighten state control of the 
economy and to retain the goal of spreading khomeinis 
fundamentalist revolution to the moslem world as a bulwark of irans 
foreign policy 
the constitutional amendments which are being formulated by a 
committee appointed by khomeini are widely expected to enhance the 
presidency with more executive powers at the expense of the prime 
ministry to eliminate competing power structures which have snarled 
the decisionmaking process for years 
that would give khamenei and rafsanjani formidable power in the 
postkhomeini era with which to fend off any challenge from the 
radicals 
