at least 373 people have been killed and 1450 wounded since the 
syrians and christians began shelling duels march 8 
both sides have ignored a ceasefire called by the arab league 
three weeks ago to end the latest round in the 14yearold civil war 
between moslem and christian forces 
a communique from christian army commander gen michel aouns 
office accused the syrian army of firing at a christian garrison in 
the hilltop town of souk elgharb southeast of beirut with tanks 
and 130mm mortars 
