become the 51st us state or seek independence 
the caribbean island of 32 million mostly spanishspeaking 
people has been a us commonwealth since 1952 
it will be the first vote on puerto ricos political status since 
1967 when 67 percent voted to remain a us commonwealth 32 
percent for statehood and less than 1 percent for independence 
puerto ricos statehood and independence parties did not actively 
participate in that vote 
sen j bennett johnston dla who presided at the senate 
