would be fundamentally different because the three status 
options would be precisely defined and the vote would be binding on 
congress 
under commonwealth puerto ricans are us citizens and eligible 
for federal benefits but they cannot vote for president the island 
received 65 billion in federal money in 1988 
the committees next round of hearings is scheduled for july 
1214 to hear the bush administrations views on the plebiscite 
president bush has said he favors statehood 
