seven kinds of loans at the end of the first quarter was 239 
percent down from 249 percent at the end of december a delinquent 
loan is defined as one in which at least one payment is past due for 
30 days or more 
lower delinquencies indicate that consumer balance sheets are 
still reasonably strong aba chief economist robert dugger said in 
a statement 
