higher than a year ago when it hit a threeyear low of 219 percent 
the district of columbia reported the lowest delinquency rate 
116 percent followed by south carolina 119 percent and 
wisconsin 126 percent the highest rates were in puerto rico 498 
percent louisiana 475 percent and north dakota 440 percent 
the seven types of loans included in the quarterly survey are 
personal direct auto indirect auto mobile home recreational 
vehicle property improvement and closedend home equity 
the lowest delinquency rate was reported on home equity loans 
