<DOCNO> AP890619-0189 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a giant spot roughly 6200 miles wide has 
been discovered on the planet neptune by the voyager 2 space probe 
and scientists said monday it looks like a storm similar to the 
great red spot on jupiter 
its huge said physicist edward stone voyager project 
scientist for nasa and a vice president of the california institute 
of technology it would be reasonable to suspect this is a large 
hurricanelike storm system similar to the great red spot 
however stone said voyager 2 still is too far from neptune to 
determine if winds are swirling within the gargantuan spot which 
measures about 6200 miles in diameter jupiters great red spot 
contains 250 mph winds 
scientists havent yet named neptunes spot but are calling it 
the dark spot because it appears darker than the surrounding 
bluegreenish atmosphere he added 
the color of the spot isnt yet known because scientists havent 
processed a complete set of pictures through different color 
filters said andrew ingersoll a caltech planetary scientist 
voyager 2 is hurtling at more than 42000 mph toward its aug 24 
close encounter with neptune at that time the hardy spacecraft 
will zip within 3000 miles of the gaseous planets cloud tops by 
far the closest of any of voyagers planetary flybys five hours 
later it will fly within 25000 miles of triton one of neptunes 
two known moons 
by tuesday voyager 2 will be nearly 266 billion miles from 
earth and 5898 million miles from neptune traveling at a speed of 
42216 mph said mary beth murrill a spokeswoman for the national 
aeronautics and space administrations jet propulsion laboratory 
the neptune encounter will be voyager 2s fourth and final 
planetary flyby since the probe was launched from cape canaveral in 
1977 it explored jupiter in 1979 saturn in 1981 and uranus in 1986 
neptunes dark spot is located at about 25 to 30 degrees latitude 
in the planets southern hemisphere ingersoll said adding that 
voyager also discovered a much smaller rapidly changing white spot 
about half the size of the dark spot at about 70 degrees south 
latitude 
stone said neptunes dark spot first was clearly recognized in 
still photographs taken by voyager 2s television cameras in april 
and can be seen faintly in pictures taken as early as january 
it isnt as large as jupiters great red spot which is 16000 
miles across at its widest point large enough to contain three 
earths but the dark spot is just as large relative to neptune 
about a fifth of the planets diameter as the great red spot is 
relative to jupiter 
jupiters great red spot was discovered more than 350 years ago 
ingersoll said it is believed to be red because of organic 
chemicals or possibly sulfur or phosphorus trapped within it 
besides the great red spot jupiter also contains dozens of 
smaller storm systems which appear as white spots and saturn also 
has similar storms although they are less visible stone said 
the major mystery of jupiters great red spot is how the storm 
has remained intact for centuries while earths hurricanes break up 
after a week or two ingersoll said 
the absence of continents on giant gas planets like jupiter and 
neptune may explain the persistence of the spots he said adding 
that continents may help dissipate hurricanes on earth 
computer simulations suggest smaller storms combine to form giant 
storms such as the red spot and neptunes dark spot stone and 
ingersoll said 
neptune is the solar systems fourth largest planet and usually 
is the eighth planet from the sun but because plutos elongated 
elliptical orbit sometimes brings it closer to the sun neptune 
currently is the ninth and most distant planet from the sun 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

