<TEXT>
here at a glance are highlights of actions 
taken monday by the supreme court 
 
drug tests 
 
the court gave railroads broader power to test their workers for 
drugs upholding routine tests for conrail employees 
by a 72 vote the justices said conrail the consolidated rail 
corporation may require the tests without permitting collective 
bargaining over the issue 
the decision marks the first time the court has ruled on drug 
testing by private employers but the ruling is based on an 
interpretation of the federal railway labor act and may not have 
sweeping impact for other workers 
the case is conrail vs railway labor executives 881 
 
christian scientist 
 
the court turned down an appeal by a california woman facing 
criminal charges in her daughters death because she tried to heal 
the child through prayer rather than seeking medical help 
the justices without comment refused to block the womans trial 
in sacramento on charges of childendangerment and involuntary 
manslaughter 
the case is walker vs superior court 881471 
 
beer prices 
 
the court struck down a connecticut law aimed at assuring that 
beer sold in the state costs no more than it does in three 
neighboring states 
by a 63 vote the court said such laws unconstitutionally 
interfere with interstate commerce 
the case is healy vs beer institute 88449 
 
power rates 
 
the court ruled unanimously that federal courts have authority to 
referee some disputes over electric power rates between public 
utilities and local or state regulatory agencies 
the justices ordered a federal court to review a claim by new 
orleans public service inc nopsi a utility seeking to pass on 
135 million in costs to its dustomers 
the case is new orleans public service vs new orleans city 
council 88348 
 
writer 
 
the court turned down an appeal by margaret randall a professor 
and writer who has been threatened with deportation from the united 
states for supporting communism 
the court without comment left intact a ruling that it is 
premature to consider the constitutional and legal issues she raised 
the case is randall vs thornburgh 881412 
 
asbestos 
 
the court barred asbestos manufacturers from suing the government 
to recover money they paid to a navy shipyard worker injured by 
inhaling the product 
the court without comment rejected an appeal by two 
manufacturers in a case from washington state 
the cases are eaglepicher vs us 881382 and raymark vs 
us 881418 
 
mandal 
 
the court refused to reinstate former maryland gov marvin 
mandels 1977 mailfraud conviction thrown out five years after he 
completed a prison term 
the court without comment rejected a bush administration appeal 
aimed at using mandels case to set guidelines on when someone may 
challenge a fraud conviction for which the sentence already was 
served 
the case is us vs mandel 881759 
 
marshall islands 
 
the court barred additional us compensation to inhabitants of 
the marshall islands for nuclear weapon testing there more than 30 
years ago 
the court without comment let stand a ruling that threw out a 
lawsuit by residents of the pacific island republic 
the case is people of enewetak vs us 881466 
 
legal fees 
 
the court in a victory for civil rights lawyers and their 
clients upheld the award of more than 4 million in legal fees to 
lawyers who won a kansas city school desegregation suit 
the justices voting 80 ruled that paralegals law clerks and 
recent law school graduates are entitled to compensation at the 
market rate for their work 
by a separate 53 vote the court said states that lose such 
cases may be forced to pay extra money to civil rights attorneys as 
compensation for a delay in payment 
the case is missouri vs jenkins 8864 
 
pollution fine 
 
the court left intact a fine of nearly 1 million against a 
maryland paper mill operator that failed to comply with a federal 
clean water laws reporting requirements 
the court without comment rejected a challenge to a key 
provision of the act authorizing citizens and environmental groups 
to sue alleged polluters 
the case is simkins vs sierra club 88660 
</TEXT>
