a school board voted unanimously 
monday night to appeal a circuit judges ruling that it improperly 
dismissed a veteran math teacher who refused to wear a tie to class 
all five mason county school board members voted to appeal the 
decision objecting to the firing of bill webb a 46yearold math 
teacher from gallipolis ohio to the west virginia supreme court 
im not upset that it will be appealed webb said before the 
board vote 
ive felt from the beginning that what they did was wrong 
said webb whose typical school clothes consisted of the blue jeans 
and flannel shirts he wears while operating his gallia county ohio 
farm and body shop across the river from point pleasant 
after the meeting board president emma kearns said the panel 
made short shrift of the appeal because board members were unanimous 
in firing webb last december 
she referred further questions to board attorney diane johnson 
who had discussed the circuit court decision with board members at a 
hearing last week 
i told them of the courts decision and my recommendation was 
to appeal johnson said 
superintendent charles chambers imposed a new dress code last 
summer after teachers had signed work contracts for the new school 
year and suspended webb three times when the 19year teacher 
refused to comply with its orders to wear a tie and dress pants 
webb was fired dec 19 on a charge of gross insubordination 
webb appealed his firing and earlier suspensions on june 7 
circuit judge charlie king ruled webb had the right to disobey the 
dress code developed by the superintendent because the latter had no 
right to develop a code separate from the board 
king also ordered the board to give webb 11 days back pay and 
pay 1000 in legal fees 
after the legality of chambers code came into question the 
board adopted a policy that made ties optional but still banned 
teachers from wearing denim or blue jeans 
board members however maintain that webb still deserved to 
fired for insubordination 
board attorney johnson had previously notified the west virginia 
supreme court of its intent to appeal but formal board action was 
required 
webb said monday he didnt expect to return to the mason county 
school system for that and other reasons 
i cant see going back with the hard feelings that are there 
webb said ive had friends that ive known for 20 years that 
dont talk to me anymore 
people see me coming and they walk right past me i dont need 
that in my life 
