editors note hes the pt barnum of west virginia politics a 
showman remembered for ridding the state of thousands of junked cars 
and bringing running water to thousands of rural homes but a james 
manchin could lose his job as state treasurer a state investment 
firm supervised by his staff lost hundreds of millions of dollars in 
the new york bond market and he faces trial by the state senate 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a james manchin west virginias 
flamboyant state treasurer whose alliterative oratory and 
distinctive dress helped make him one of the states most popular 
politicians is in the fight of his life 
manchin whose theatrics have brought him both fame and derision 
has been impeached by state house of delegates and faces trial in 
the state senate on july 10 over the loss of hundreds of millions of 
dollars from a state investment fund his office supervised 
if twothirds of the 34 senators vote against him the 
62yearold former high school coach will be removed from office and 
could lose his pension 
a man who never met anyone he didnt know and who never found a 
word he couldnt squeeze into a mangled metaphor manchin 
acknowledges his reputation as something of a clown could be working 
against him 
so what it made me he says you cant have it both ways 
i think maybe im an easy target and you have to understand 
ive made a lot of enemies 
the son of italian immigrants manchin has been a legislator 
teacher state director of the farmers home admininstration 
secretary of state and state treasurer 
but it was during his tenure as director of reap the 
rehabilitation environmental action program created to rid the 
state of junked cars and abandoned appliances that manchin became 
a household name 
he appeared on posters made public service commercials and was 
the subject of a song he claimed the program rid the state of 
100000 junked cars but later acknowledged the total was about 
30000 
wearing his traditional dark suits bow ties and a hat usually a 
widebrimmed white fedora manchin took his show on the road posing 
atop rusted junkers with a sledgehammer and proclaiming to the 
assembled television cameras that he intended to remove these 
jezebels of junkery mash this mess of muckery or eliminate 
this truculent trash 
if he couldnt find the right word manchin made one up 
we come to report that reap will not relapse into a reverie of 
remoteness but will press ever harder to save a world which is bent 
on drowning itself in a deluge of debris he said in one fit of 
alliteration on another day he proclaimed that reap will not 
fiddle while cub scouts on a camping trip fizzle in filthery 
i was the original 30second sound bite let us do battle 
against this bastion of bacteria manchin said during an 
interview in his cluttered office well you can say that in 30 
seconds because how do you explain anything in 30 seconds 
you know why people knew me it was entertaining look at that 
clown so weve got that kind of reputation and i dont mind it 
in the years since then manchin has toned down his rhetoric 
although he still tends to end his correspondence including press 
releases with the phrase may the bright morning star be a lamp 
unto our feet 
the lobby to his office resembles a flea market with two 9foot 
bookcases loaded with dozens of volunteer fire department helmets a 
display of different types of us currency a stack of sheet music 
of the state song and the remnants of a flea circus manchin rescued 
from the capitol basement 
on his office wall along with a framed drawing of the statue of 
liberty and paintings of his parents jesus and presidents harry 
truman and franklin d roosevelt is a plaque that quotes teddy 
roosevelt 
far better it is to dare mighty things to win glorious 
triumphs even though checkered by failure than to take rank with 
those poor spirits who neither enjoy much nor suffer much because 
they live in the gray twilight that knows no victory nor defeat 
three months after manchin received that plaque from his staff in 
january 1987 the treasurers investment staff ran into trouble 
while living by that creed trying to maintain phenomenal interest 
earnings on its investments sometimes averaging 14 percent or more 
by trading heavily in the new york bond market the treasurers 
employees began to fail and fail big 
in one month the investment staff had lost 100 million from the 
18 billion fund former gov arch moore before leaving office 
last january said the losses eventually totaled 279 million 
manchin says they totaled 231 million 
manchin says he was never told of the losses until auditors made 
them public the house of delegates voting 6534 in march to 
impeach him on 17 counts said either he knew and did nothing to 
stop them or else he didnt know but should have 
manchins supporters call him the peoples servant always ready 
to hear their complaints about any facet of state government and do 
his best to find a solution his opponents call him a buffoon who 
spends more time traveling around the state handing out cheap 
trinkets and making speeches than doing his job testimony during 
house impeachment procedings placed him out of the office up to 
three out of every five days 
everybody plays on the fact that well if i had been here 
more im here as much as any public official because i take 
care of my responsibilities manchin says 
</TEXT>
