but didnt become public until december 1988 after he had been 
reelected without opposition 
despite his political problems manchin remains the man many 
people want to see when they visit the state capitol tour groups 
make his office a regular stop and manchin expresses disappointment 
if he is tied up on a telephone call and cant greet a group of 
junior high school students before they leave for other parts of the 
capitol his office handles hundreds of phone calls a day from 
people inquiring about every type of government service from tax 
refunds to road repairs he has a fulltime ombudsman on his staff 
whether its network television national magazines local 
newspapers or public speakers no one is safe from manchins 
wellpublicized wrath if he perceives a slur on his native state 
an insult of insane proportions is how he once described a 
magazine advertisement for hot dogs that he said unfairly depicted 
west virginians as dirty he once said nbc faced the winds of 
war because today show weatherman willard scotts map of the 
united states omitted west virginias northern panhandle 
hes been constantly criticized by lawmakers for spending his 
budget on ceremonial certificates and other doodads naming 
recipients commodore of the ship of state or public friend no 
1 he holds an annual ceremony so he can award his order of the 
35th star to senior citizens 
sometimes riding on an elephant or being on top of a junked 
car or using alliteration clowning around it gets attention 
manchin said 
the point were trying to make is that i have a sense of humor 
i am a james manchin im not cloned of anybody im not going to 
be one im going to be who i am 
and when they lay me away on a hill in farmington wva 
theyll say here lies a james manchin he loved his god he loved 
his state he loved his family and he did it all and said it all 
 
