<TEXT>
if theres one thing american automakers 
should be able to do better than japanese rivals its knowing the 
styles american drivers like 
but japans automakers set out to eliminate that advantage by 
establishing design shops in that carcrazed corner of america 
southern california theyve turned out the snazzy prototypes for 
bestsellers like mazdas mx5 miata nissans pathfinder 4x4 
hondas crx and toyotas celica 
the americandesigned japanese cars were so successful that 
detroit was forced to follow suit with its own california design 
studios 
as is increasingly the case in the knowledge economy the big 
three us carmakers found that to stay in the race even in their 
own backyard they have to get smarter about giving consumers what 
they want 
they were too insulated from the popular culture they were 
still living mentally and psychologically in the bloomfield hills 
