pasadena where many car designers get their start people are 
less inhibited to look at the new to express themselves in ways 
theyre not so capable of doing in other parts of the country or the 
world 
among the auto trends traced to california hot rods pickup 
trucks as basic commuter transportation convertible pickups trim 
and grillwork thats painted not chromed the new emphasis on 
comfortable interiors 
nissans pulsar nx a compact with interchangeable tops that 
makes it a convertible a pickup or a station wagon emerged in 
production almost unchanged from the design said gerald hirshberg 
a former gm designer who heads the companys studio in la jolla 
the same was true for the companys brawny americanlooking 
pathfinder 4x4 and hardbody pickups 
mazdas studio employs designers from japan the united states 
and taiwan several have worked in europe 
nissans hirshberg has found the japanese admire their american 
coworkers willingness to take risks in design while the americans 
are taken aback by the japanese ability to translate a design into a 
practical car 
theres a kind of subtle collaboration that can only happen 
