a federal bankruptcy judge issued a 
restraining order monday to temporarily block developer donald 
trumps 63 million bid to buy the debtridden elsinore atlantis 
casino hotel in atlantic city nj 
us district court judge rosemary gambardella issued the 10day 
order after a brief hearing ruling that irreparable harm and 
injury will result if the deal is allowed to proceed without 
additional hearings 
creditors hold a 65 million mortgage on three atlantis parking 
lots they requested the order preventing new jerseys casino 
control commission a stateappointed conservator and elsinore shore 
associates owners of the boardwalk property from transferring the 
property to trump 
the judge scheduled a hearing for june 29 she will then consider 
extending the restraining order and whether or not additional bids 
should be solicited for the failing property 
